## 3. Project Layout (feature-based)

Code is organized **by feature**, not by technical layer. Cross-cutting code lives in `shared/`; bootstrap and route wiring live in `app/`.

```
backoffice/
├── electron/                          # main + preload (not under src/)
│   ├── main.ts                        # BrowserWindow, safeStorage IPC handlers
│   └── preload.ts                     # exposes window.staffStorage
├── electron.vite.config.ts
├── src/
│   ├── main.tsx                       # renderer entry
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── app/                           # composition only — no feature logic
│   │   ├── App.tsx                    # QueryClient → AuthProvider → SplashGate → Router
│   │   ├── router.tsx                 # route table + guards
│   │   ├── query-client.ts
│   │   └── global.css                 # :root design tokens (--manda-*)
│   ├── shared/
│   │   ├── theme/manda-theme.ts       # TS palette (prefer CSS vars for styling)
│   │   ├── ui/                        # design-system atoms (*.tsx + *.module.css)
│   │   └── api/                       # axios client, ApiError
│   └── features/
│       ├── auth/                      # staff login/session
│       │   ├── api/                   # staff-auth.ts, types.ts
│       │   ├── storage/               # staff-storage.ts (IPC wrapper)
│       │   ├── providers/             # auth-provider.tsx
│       │   ├── components/            # guards, login-form, splash-gate
│       │   ├── pages/                 # login-page
│       │   └── index.ts               # public exports (useAuth, guards, LoginPage)
│       └── shell/                     # authenticated chrome (sidebar, topbar, home)
│           ├── components/
│           └── pages/
└── .env.example                       # VITE_API_URL
```

### Feature boundary rules

| Rule                       | Detail                                                                                                      |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Feature owns its domain    | Each `features/<name>/` folder owns `api/`, `components/`, `pages/`, `providers/`, `hooks/` as needed       |
| No cross-feature internals | e.g. `features/shell/` imports `useAuth` from `features/auth/index.ts` — not deep paths into auth internals |
| `shared/` is generic       | Tokens, UI atoms, HTTP infra — no KYC/transaction/staff business rules                                      |
| `app/` wires only          | Providers, router — no forms, no API calls                                                                  |
| Future features            | `features/kyc/`, `features/transactions/` added in later phases with the same layout                        |

