## 6. Staff Auth Lifecycle

`features/auth/providers/auth-provider.tsx` exposes `useAuth()`:

```ts
{
  status: "loading" | "unauthenticated" | "authenticated",
  staff: StaffProfile | null,
  bootstrapped: boolean,
  loginMutation,
  logoutMutation,
}
```

**Flow:**

1. Bootstrap — `staffStorage.load()` via preload IPC on mount
2. `/staff/auth/me` query — enabled when `bootstrapped && hasTokens`; `retry: false`, `staleTime: 60s`
3. Status — `loading` until bootstrap; `unauthenticated` if no tokens or `me` errored; `authenticated` on success
4. Auth-lost listener — axios client calls back on refresh failure → clear tokens + drop `me` query
5. Login — `login` → save tokens → invalidate `me`
6. Logout — best-effort `POST /staff/auth/logout` → `staffStorage.clear()`

---

## 7. API Client (`shared/api/client.ts`)

### Endpoints (staff namespace)

| Call    | Method | Path                  | Notes                                          |
| ------- | ------ | --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| login   | POST   | `/staff/auth/login`   | no bearer                                      |
| me      | GET    | `/staff/auth/me`      | staff JWT                                      |
| refresh | POST   | `/staff/auth/refresh` | bare `refreshClient`, no interceptor recursion |
| logout  | POST   | `/staff/auth/logout`  | bearer + `{ refreshToken }`                    |

### Interceptor rules

- Skip Bearer on `/staff/auth/login` and `/staff/auth/refresh`
- On 401 (non-auth route, not retried): `refreshOnce()` → retry original request
- Refresh failure: `staffStorage.clear()` + `authLostListener()`
- Rejections normalize to `ApiError(message, status, body?)` — display Portuguese API messages directly

### Base URL

`VITE_API_URL` from `.env` (default `http://localhost:3000`). Dev CORS: ensure `http://localhost:5173` is in api `CORS_ORIGINS`.

---

## 8. Token Storage

| Layer                                               | Responsibility                                                     |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Main (`electron/main.ts`)                           | Encrypt/decrypt with `safeStorage`; read/write `staff-tokens.json` |
| Preload (`electron/preload.ts`)                     | `contextBridge.exposeInMainWorld('staffStorage', …)`               |
| Renderer (`features/auth/storage/staff-storage.ts`) | `load/save/clear` calling `window.staffStorage`                    |

Keys are distinct from end-user mobile: encrypted payload holds `accessToken` + `refreshToken`. **Never** persist tokens in `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, or React state.

---

## 9. Styling

| Rule                | Detail                                                                                                |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| CSS modules         | Co-located `*.module.css` per component/page                                                          |
| Design tokens       | `:root { --manda-green: … }` in `src/app/global.css` — use `var(--manda-*)` in modules                |
| No inline styles    | Avoid `style={{ … }}` for layout/theme; exception: dynamic CSS custom properties (avatar hash colors) |
| Shared atoms        | `shared/ui/` — `PrimaryButton`, `TextField`, `Avatar`, `MandaGlyph`, `MandaWordmark`, `LoadingScreen` |
| Prototype reference | `tmp/manda/screens-backoffice.jsx` for visual intent (not copy-paste JSX styles)                      |

---

## 10. TanStack Query Defaults (`app/query-client.ts`)

Same policy as mobile: **never retry 4xx**, retry transient errors up to 2×, `refetchOnWindowFocus: false`, mutations `retry: false`.

---

## 11. Conventions

- **File naming:** kebab-case (`auth-provider.tsx`, `login-page.module.css`)
- **Imports:** prefer `@/...` over deep relatives
- **Strict TypeScript:** fix at source, no `as any`
- **No business logic in route files** — keep `app/router.tsx` thin; logic in features
- **All HTTP via `shared/api` + feature `api/`** — never raw `fetch`/`axios` in components
- **Error display:** show `ApiError.message` (Portuguese from API)
- **Tests:** Vitest in `src/**/*.spec.ts`; UI-only changes use explicit manual checklist when no harness exists

---

## 12. Run / Build

```bash
# Terminal 1 — backend
cd manda && docker compose up postgres redis api

# Terminal 2 — seed staff (once)
STAFF_SEED_EMAIL=admin@manda.ao STAFF_SEED_PASSWORD='…' pnpm --filter api staff:seed

# Terminal 3 — backoffice
cd backoffice && npm install && npm run dev
```

```bash
npm test          # vitest
npm run build     # electron-vite production build
npm run preview   # preview packaged renderer + electron
```

Ensure `manda/.env` has `STAFF_JWT_SECRET` (32+ chars, distinct from `JWT_SECRET`).

